				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Drift...<a name="59011"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 25 04 5:39 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The CTRL key makes you run straight while it's held down while in a autocircle(I'm at work ATM so can't see what its mapped to.... I think it may be trying to strafe.. don't know for sure though).  The tap duration should be short, shorter taps will keep those mobs from getting a hold of you.... especially if they have a long reach.  
<br />

<br />
Besides the direction your looking, drift can be caused by objects forcing your camera view to pull in closer to you because the camera is against the wall.  The worst form of drift is caused by kiting in locations that are not flat.  If I hear sound (the kind you hear when you jump off something) from the game, I know I will drift dramatically (I believe uphill).  The one time I tried an auto-circle with one edge of my circle on a fairly steep hill it sucked me onto the hill.  I tried to repair it with CTRL but in 4-5 circles it screwed up my circle enough to get me killed.  Live and learn.... or in my case DIE and learn.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
